@AGENTS.md

Everything a coding agent needs to know about how to behave in this repo
lives in `AGENTS.md` (imported above) — that file is tool-agnostic on
purpose, so Claude Code, Codex, and any other agent read the same operating
guide. Don't add project-wide instructions here; add them to `AGENTS.md`
instead. This file exists only to satisfy Claude Code's convention of
loading `CLAUDE.md`.
